concrete houses, while the fourth takes up the thousands of migrants who attempt, sometimes with tragic results, to cross the Mediterranean on rickety boats in search of new opportunities. The resulting book offers a remarkable portrait of contemporary Senegal and a means of theorizing mobility and its impossibilities far beyond the African continent.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aSocial mobilityxSenegalxDakar. 0aSocial mobilityzSenegalzDakar. 70(DE-588)4026944-90(DE-627)1044271240(DE-576)208968601aInfrastruktur2gnd 70(DE-588)4033229-90(DE-627)1041378000(DE-576)209000694aKritik2gnd 70(DE-588)4039785-30(DE-627)1062266220(DE-576)209036621aMobilität2gnd 70(DE-588)4041169-20(DE-627)1062203300(DE-576)209043687aNahverkehr2gnd 70(DE-588)4063234-90(DE-627)1061286980(DE-576)20914789XaVerstädterung2gnd 70(DE-588)4066796-00(DE-627)1041973230(DE-576)209166339aWohnungspolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4127960-80(DE-627)1044265780(DE-576)209598042aHauptstadt2gnd 70(DE-588)4130642-90(DE-627)1057010410(DE-576)209620706aLebensbedingungen2gnd 70(DE-588)4138964-50(DE-627)1056387570(DE-576)209690445aStadtbevölkerung2gnd 70(DE-588)4152886-40(DE-627)10553501X0(DE-576)209799056aErschließung2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aAfrica.  aCitizenship.  aInfrastructure.  aMigration.  aMobility.  aSenegal.  aState.  aStructural Adjustment.  aTransnationalism.  aUrban Space.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311071193608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUrban Studies and Social Rights eBook Package PP 2016-2019z978311063851640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226489063423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226489063/original  a978-3-11-063851-6  Ur